thchild]] (UK) - ''[[Stakk Attakk]]''\n* Wyzard - ''Knights of Metal'' (EP)\n* [[Mark Slaughter|Xcursion]] - ''Ready to Roll''\n* [[Y&T]] - ''[[In Rock We Trust]]''\n* [[Zebra (American band)|Zebra]] - ''[[No Tellin' Lies]]''\n* [[Znowhite]] - ''[[All Hail to Thee]]'' (EP)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Events==\n* [[Def Leppard]]'s drummer [[Rick Allen (drummer)|Rick Allen]] loses his left arm in a car accident on December 31.\n* [[Deep Purple]] reunite.\n* [[Hanoi Rocks]] drummer [[Razzle (musician)|Razzle]] is killed in an automobile accident in early December. The driver of the car is [[Vince Neil]] of [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]].\n* The debut albums of both [[Saint Vitus (band)|Saint Vitus]] (''[[Saint Vitus (album)|Saint Vitus]]'') and [[Trouble (band)|Trouble]] (''[[Psalm 9 (album)|Psalm 9]]'') are released.\n* ''[[This is Spinal Tap]]'', a cult mockumentary directed by [[Rob Reiner]] about the semi-fictional band [[Spinal Tap (band)|Spinal Tap]], is released.\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1983 in heavy metal music|1983]]|after=[[1985 in heavy metal music|1985]]|year='''1984'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1984 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1984 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in music|1984}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1984|heavy metal music}}\nThis is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in the year 1984.\n\n==Events==\n*October 23 \u2014 A debate over heavy metal music occurs on [[Sveriges Television|SVT:s]] ''[[Svar direkt]]'' between [[Anders Tegn\u00e9r]] and [[Siewert \u00d6holm]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kristianstadsbladet.se/bromolla/sveriges-mest-kanda-klipp/|title=Sveriges mest k\u00e4nda klipp|publisher=Kristianstadsbladet|language=Swedish|author=Roger Bing|date=4 June 2015|accessdate=3 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n* [[Agent Steel]]\n*[[Angel Dust (band)|Angel Dust]] \n* [[Annihilator (band)|Annihilator]]\n* [[Atheist (band)|Atheist]]\n* [[Blind Guardian]]  (under the name \"Lucifer's Heritage\" until 1988)\n* [[Candlemass (band)|Candlemass]]\n* [[Celtic Frost]]\n*[[Chastain (band)|Chastain]] \n*[[Cryptic Slaughter]]\n*[[Deceased (band)|Deceased]] \n*[[Detente (band)|Detente]] \n* [[Eudoxis]]\n*[[Heathen (band)|Heathen]]\n* [[Helloween]]\n*[[Hirax]]\n* [[Keel (band)|Keel]]\n* [[King Kobra]]\n* [[Living Colour]]\n*[[Tony MacAlpine]]\n*[[Massacre (metal band)|Massacre]] \n* [[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]]\n*[[Morbid Saint]]\n* [[Nepal (band)|Nepal]]\n* [[Nuclear Assault]]\n* [[Primus (band)|Primus]]\n*[[Racer X (band)|Racer X]] \n* [[Rage (German band)|Rage]] (under the name \"Avenger\" until 1986)\n*[[Sacrilege (band)|Sacrilege]]\n* [[Sadus]]\n* [[Sepultura]]\n*[[Slaughter (Canadian band)|Slaughter]] \n* [[Soundgarden]]\n* [[Stratovarius]]\n*[[Thanatos (band)|Thanatos]] \n* [[Uncle Slam]] (known as The Brood until 1987)\n* [[Warrant (American band)|Warrant]]\n* [[Whiplash (band)|Whiplash]]\n*[[Wolfsbane (band)|Wolfsbane]] \n\n==Reformed bands==\n* [[Deep Purple]]\n\n==Albums & EPs==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Lee Aaron]] - ''[[Metal Queen]]''\n* [[AC/DC]] - ''[['74 Jailbreak]]'' (EP)\n* [[Alcatrazz]] - ''[[Live Sentence]]'' (live)\n* [[The Angels (Australian band)|The Angels]], aka Angel City - ''[[Two Minute Warning]]''\n* [[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]] - ''[[Fistful of Metal]]''\n* Antix - ''Get Up, Get Happy'' (EP)\n* [[April Wine]] - ''[[Animal Grace]]''\n* Armed Forces - ''Let There Be Metal'' (EP)\n* [[Armored Saint]] - ''[[March of the Saint]]''\n* Attentat Rock \u2013 ''Le Gang des Saigneurs''\n* [[Autograph (American band)|Autograph]] - ''[[Sign In Please]]''\n* [[Avenger (British band)|Avenger (UK)]] - ''[[Blood Sports (album)|Blood Sports]]''\n* Axe Victims - ''Another Victim''\n* [[Axewitch|Axe Witch]] - ''[[Visions of the Past]]''\n* Baby Tuckoo - '