 of both [[Saint Vitus (band)|Saint Vitus]] (''[[Saint Vitus (album)|Saint Vitus]]'') and [[Trouble (band)|Trouble]] (''[[Psalm 9 (album)|Psalm 9]]'') are released.\n* ''[[This is Spinal Tap]]'', a cult mockumentary directed by [[Rob Reiner]] about the semi-fictional band [[Spinal Tap (band)|Spinal Tap]], is released.\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1983 in heavy metal music|1983]]|after=[[1985 in heavy metal music|1985]]|year='''1984'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1984 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1984 in music|Metal]]\n", "name_user": "Metalmaniac87", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNewly formed bands", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1984_in_heavy_metal_music"}
{"title_page": "Visa requirements for United States citizens", "text_new": " [[File:Us-passport.jpg|thumb|A [[United States passport]] with biometric chip.]]\n'''Visa requirements for [[United States citizen]]s''' and '''[[U.S. national|non-citizen nationals]]''' are administrative entry restrictions by the authorities of [[Sovereign state|other states]] placed on citizens of the United States.\n\n{{As of|2020|04|07|post=,}} holders of a [[United States passport]] could travel to 185 countries and territories without a [[travel visa]], or with a visa on arrival. The [[United States passport]] currently ranks{{refn|group=Note|name=Ranking| Using [[Ranking#Dense ranking (\"1223\" ranking)|dense ranking]].}} 8th in terms of travel freedom (tied with the passports of Belgium, Switzerland, Norway and the UK) according to the [[Henley Passport Index]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Global Ranking \u2013 Visa Passport Index|url=https://www.henleypassportindex.com/assets/2020/Q1/2020%20HPI%20and%20Global%20Mobility%20Report_200107.pdf|publisher=Henley & Partners|accessdate=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==2020 travel restrictions==\n{{main|Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n[[File:USA Travel Restrictions from COVID-19.svg|thumb|600px|Countries that have imposed some form of travel restrictions on US Citizens and/or travel from the United States]]\nAs a result of the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], several countries have imposed temporary travel restrictions on United States citizens or persons arriving from the United States.<ref name=\"IATA\">[https://www.iatatravelcentre.com/international-travel-document-news/1580226297.htm CORONAVIRUS OUTBREAK IN CHINA (PEOPLE'S REP.) - UPDATE], International Air Transport Association Travel Centre</ref>\n*{{flag|Argentina}} \u2014 Admission refused, except residents.\n*{{flag|Austria}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Australia}} \u2014 Admission suspended for non Australians except for Family connection\n*{{flag|Belgium}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Bermuda}} \u2014 14-day self-quarantine required.\n*{{flag|Botswana}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Brazil}} \u2014 Admission refused unless exempt until April 30.<ref>https://br.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|Brunei}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Cambodia}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Canada}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonessential travel.\n*{{flag|Chile}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonessential travel.\n*{{flag|Croatia}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonresidents.\n*{{flag|Cyprus}} \u2014 Admission refused with few exceptions until April 10.<ref>https://cy.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|Colombia}} \u2014 Admission refused, except residents who perform an obligatory 14-day period of self isolation.\n*{{flag|Costa Rica}} \u2014 Admission refused until April 30, except residents, who are subject to mandatory 14-day quarantine.<ref>https://cr.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|Czech Republic}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Denmark}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods. Entry refused into Greenland and Faroe Islands until April 13.\n*{{flag|El Salvador}} \u2014 Admission refused, except accredited diplomats and legal residents.\n*{{flag|Estonia}} \u2014 Admission refused effective March 17. Right of entry will remain for citizens and those with a right of residence, as well as foreign citizens whose next of kin live in Estonia. Transit is allowed for foreigners not showing signs of the coronavirus. A mandatory two-week quarantine will be set for anyone entering the country.\n*{{flag|France}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Georgia (country)}} - Admission refused until April 21st, except dependents of citizens and diplomats.\n*{{flag|Germany}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Greece}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Guatemala}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Hong Kong}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonessential travel.\n*{{flag|Honduras}} \u2014 Admission refused.<ref>https://hn.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|Hungary}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Iceland}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|India}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Indonesia}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Italy}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Israel}} \u2014 Admission refused, except by specific permit for non-residents. All entrants must remain under home isolation for 14 days.\n*{{flag|Latvia}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Liechtenstein}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Lithuania}} \u2014 Admission refused, except those with residence permit.\n*{{flag|Luxembourg}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Macau}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Malaysia}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonresidents. Quarantine required for residents. \n*{{flag|Malta}} \u2014 14-day quarantine required.\n*{{flag|Mongolia}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Netherlands}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|New Zealand}} \u2014 14-day self-isolation required.\n*{{flag|North Korea}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Norway}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Oman}} \u2014 Tourist visas suspended until April 30.\n*{{flag|Panama}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Philippines}} \u2014 Admission refused, except spouses and children of Filipino nationals. <ref>https://ph.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|Poland}} \u2014 Admission refused until April 30, except for those possessing residence or work permits. 14 days quarantine required.\n*{{flag|Russia}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Singapore}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonresidents. Quarantine required for residents. \n*{{flag|Slovakia}} \u2014 Admission refused for nonresidents. Quarantine required for residents. \n*{{flag|Slovenia}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|South Africa}} \u2014 visitors who have been in, transited through, or are nationals of several designated \"high-risk countries\" (including the United States) are not allowed to enter.<ref name=\"ZA-2019-nCov\" />\n*{{flag|Spain}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Suriname}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Sweden}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Switzerland}} \u2014 Admission to [[Schengen Area]] refused from noon 17 March until April 30, except residents, family members of EU citizens, medical personnel, and people responsible for transport of goods.\n*{{flag|Tajikistan}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Thailand}} \u2014 Admission refused, except residents.\n*{{flag|Turkmenistan}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Ukraine}} \u2014 Admission refused, except residents.<ref>https://ua.usembassy.gov/covid-19-information/</ref>\n*{{flag|UAE}} \u2014 Visa issuance suspended for non-diplomatic passport holders.\n*{{flag|UK}} \u2014 Travel Restricted<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/international-travel/International-Travel-Country-Information-Pages/UnitedKingdom.html|title=United Kingdom International Travel Information|website=travel.state.gov|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n*{{flag|Venezuela}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n*{{flag|Vietnam}} \u2014 Admission refused.\n\n==Visa requirements map==\n[[File:Visa requirements for United States citizens.png|thumb|upright=3.7|center|Visa requirements for holders of regular United States passports {{legend|#ed1c24|United States}}{{legend|#22b14c|Visa free access}}{{legend|#B5E61D|Visa issued upon arrival}}{{lege