/australia-opens-biometric-smartgate-programme-to-us-citizens/|title=Australia opens biometric 'SmartGate' programme to US citizens - Planet Biometrics News|publisher=}}</ref>\n|{{yes|\u221a}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Austria}}\n| {{yes|Visa not required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=AT|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=ETA>{{cite web|title=Electronic Travel Authority (Subclass 601)|url=http://www.immi.gov.au/visas/visitor/601/|publisher=Department of Immigration and Border Protection|accessdate=25 September 2013}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|90}}90 days\n|\n*90 days within any 180-day period in the [[Schengen Area]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Austria Country Specific Information \u2013 Entry/Exit Requirements for U.S. Citizens|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/english/country/austria.html|publisher=Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State|accessdate=18 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201171906/http://travel.state.gov/content/passports/english/country/austria.html#|archive-date=2014-02-01|url-status=dead}}</ref> Beginning in January 2021, [[ETIAS]] system will become mandatory for all Non-EU international travellers.<ref name=\"europa.eu-1\">{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/dgs/home-affairs/what-we-do/policies/european-agenda-security/legislative-documents/docs/20161116/proposal_etias_en.pdf|title=Proposal for a REGULATION OF THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND OF THE COUNCIL establishing a European Travel Information and Authorisation System (ETIAS) and amending Regulations (EU) No 515/2014, (EU) 2016/399, (EU) 2016/794 and (EU) 2016/1624|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/here-s-what-you-need-to-know-about-the-new-travel-restrictions-to-europe-1.4335968|title=ETIAS rules: Europe travel restrictions have changed for Canadians &#124; CTV News|website=www.ctvnews.ca}}</ref>\n|{{yes|\u221a}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Azerbaijan}}\n| {{Optional|eVisa / Visa on arrival}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=AZ|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|30}}30 days<ref>{{cite web|url=https://evisa.gov.az|title=Home Page -         The Electronic Visa System of Azerbaijan Republic|website=evisa.gov.az}}</ref>\n|\n*If intending to stay in the Republic of Azerbaijan for more than ten days, the visitor must register at the [http://www.migration.gov.az State Migration Service] of the Republic of Azerbaijan within three days upon arrival in Azerbaijan.<ref>\"[http://www.azembassy.us/visa-service/important-notice.html Important Notice to Foreign Visitors]\". ''[[Embassy of Azerbaijan, Washington, D.C.]]'' Retrieved 21 May 2017.</ref>\n*Applicants of Armenian ancestry or with Armenian visas in their passport may not obtain a visa.<ref>{{cite web|title=Azerbaijan Country Specific Information \u2013 Entry/Exit Requirements for U.S. Citizens|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/english/country/azerbaijan.html|publisher=Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State|accessdate=18 November 2013}}</ref>\n*Can obtain a 30 days visa on arrival only if arriving on a direct flight of [[Azerbaijan Airlines]] from [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azembassy.us/|title=Embassy of the Republic of Azerbaijan - Embassy of Azerbaijan|publisher=}}</ref>\n|{{no|X}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Bahamas}}\n| {{yes|Visa not required}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=BS|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bahamas, The Country Specific Information \u2013 Entry/Exit Requirements for U.S. Citizens|url=https://travel.state.gov/content/passports/en/country/the-bahamas.html|publisher=Bureau of Consular Affairs, U.S. Department of State|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|240}}8 months   \n|\n*Passport Card or Enhanced Drivers License valid for Sea Travel\n|{{no|X}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Bahrain}}\n| {{Optional|eVisa / Visa on arrival}}<ref>{{Timatic|nationality=US|destination=BH|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n| {{ntsh|14}}14 days<