{"title_page": "635th Supply Chain Operations Wing", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox military unit\n|unit_name=635th Supply Chain Operations Wing\n|image= \n|caption=\n|dates=1966-1976; 2008-present\n|country=[[United States]]\n|branch=[[United States Air Force|Air Force]]\n|type=Logistics Operations\n|command_structure=[[Air Force Sustainment Center]]\n|current_commander= Col Robert Henderson\n|garrison=[[Scott Air Force Base]]\n|nickname=Smiling Bulls\n|motto= \"One call\" \n|mascot=Tigers\n|decorations=[[Air Force Outstanding Unit Award]] w/[[Combat \"V\" Device]] [[Gallantry Cross (Vietnam)|Vietnamese Gallantry Cross with Palm]]\n|notable_commanders=[https://www.af.mil/About-Us/Biographies/Display/Article/108893/major-general-mark-k-johnson/ Col Mark K. Johnson]\n|anniversaries=9 Apr\n<!-- Insignia -->\n|identification_symbol=[[File:635 Supply Chain Operations Wg.jpg|175px]]\n|identification_symbol_label=635th Supply Chain Operations Wing emblem (approved 7 March 1968)<ref name=635SCOWfacts>{{cite web |url=http://www.afhra.af.mil/About-Us/Fact-Sheets/Display/Article/432534/635-supply-chain-operations-wing-afmc/ |last1=Robertson|first1=Patsy|title=Factsheet 635 Supply Chain Operations Wing (AFMC)|date=December 8, 2010|publisher=Air Force Historical Research Agency|url-status=live |accessdate=May 5, 2014}}</ref><ref>Revised 26 August 2010 to put current unit designation on scroll.</ref>\n|identification_symbol_2=\n|identification_symbol_2_label=\n}}\n\nThe '''635th Supply Chain Operations Wing''', [[United States Air Force]], is a logistics [[wing (air force unit)|wing]]. It reports to the [[Air Force Sustainment Center]], part of [[Air Force Materiel Command]], and serves as the Air Force's new supply chain manager headquartered at [[Scott Air Force Base]], [[Illinois]]. It is an associate tenant at the base.\n\n==History==\nThe wing was originally activated at [[U-Tapao Royal Thai Navy Airfield]] in June 1966<ref name=635SCOWfacts/> as the [[Pacific Air Forces]] support organization for operations from the base, primarily the [[Strategic Air Command]] Young Tiger Task Force.\n\nActivated as the headquarters for the Mobility Air Forces Logistics Support Center (redesignated 635th Supply Chain Management Group) and the Combat Air Forces Logistics Support Center (redesignated 735th Supply Chain Management Group) in 2008.\n\nIts units now include the:\n* 635th Supply Chain Operations Group, [[Scott Air Force Base]], Illinois\n* 735th Supply Chain Operations Group, [[Langley Air Force Base]], Virginia\n* 635th Materiel Maintenance Group, [[Holloman Air Force Base]], New Mexico\n* Detachment 1, Air Force Petroleum Office, [[Ft. Belvoir]], Virginia\n\n==Lineage==\n* Constituted as the '''635th Combat Support Group''' on 17 May 1966 and activated (not organized)\n: Organized on 8 July 1966\n: Redesignated '''635th Aerospace Support Group''' on 30 January 1976\n: Inactivated on 20 June 1976\n* Redesignated '''635th Supply Chain Management Wing''' on 12 March 2008\n: Activated on 1 April 2008\n: Redesignated '''635th Supply Chain Operations Wing''' on 30 June 2010<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n\n===Assignments===\n* [[Pacific Air Forces]], 17 May 1966 (not organized)\n* [[Thirteenth Air Force]], 8 July 1966\n* [[17th Air Division]], 1 July 1975\n* Thirteenth Air Force, 1 January 1976 - 20 June 1976\n* [[Air Force Global Logistics Support Center]], 1 April 2008 (attached to Air Force Sustainment Center after 11 July 2012)\n* Air Force Sustainment Center, 1 October 2012 \u2013 present<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n\n===Stations===\n* U Tapao Royal Thai Navy Airfield, Thailand 8 July 1966 - 20 June 1976\n* [[Scott Air Force Base]], Illinois, 1 April 2008 \u2013 present<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n\n===Components===\n\n====Groups====\n* 635th Supply Chain Management Group (later 635th Supply Chain Operations Group), 1 April 2008 - \n* 735th Supply Chain Management Group (later 735th Supply Chain Operations Group), 1 April 2008 -\n\n====Squadrons====\n* 635th Air Police Squadron (later 635th Security Police Squadron), 8 July 1966 - 20 June 1976\n* 635th Civil Engineering Squadron, 8 July 1966 - 20 June 1976\n* 635th Munitions Maintenance Squadron, 15 May 1967 - 20 June 1976\n* 635th Services Squadron, 8 July 1966 - 28 February 1975\n* 635th Supply Squadron, 8 July 1966 - 20 June 1976\n\n====Other====\n* 11th USAF Dispensary (later 11th USAF Hospital), 8 July 1966 - 20 June 1976\n\n===Awards and campaigns===\n{{unit awards table\n|award_image1=AF OUA w/ v\n|award_name1=[[Air Force Outstanding Unit Award]] w/[[Combat \"V\" Device]]\n|award_date1=8 July 1966-30 June 1968\n|award_notes1=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image2=AF OUA w/ v\n|award_name2=Air Force Outstanding Unit Award w/Combat \"V\" Device\n|award_date2=1 January 1970-30 May 1971\n|award_notes2=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image3=AF OUA w/ v\n|award_name3=Air Force Outstanding Unit Award w/Combat \"V\" Device\n|award_date3=1 June 1971-31 May 1972\n|award_notes3=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image4=AF OUA w/ v\n|award_name4=Air Force Outstanding Unit Award w/Combat \"V\" Device\n|award_date4=1 June 1972-31 March 1973\n|award_notes4=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image5=AF OUA w/ v\n|award_name5=Air Force Outstanding Unit Award w/Combat \"V\" Device\n|award_date5=1 April 1973-31 March 1974\n|award_notes5=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image6=VGC\n|award_name6=[[Gallantry Cross (Vietnam)|Vietnamese Gallantry Cross with Palm]]\n|award_date6=8 July 1966-28 January 1973\n|award_notes6=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n|award_image7=VGC\n|award_name7=[[Gallantry Cross (Vietnam)|Vietnamese Gallantry Cross with Palm]]\n|award_date7=29 April 1975-30 April 1975\n|award_notes7=635th Combat Support Group<ref name=635SCOWfacts/>\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"backgrou